title.rendered: Ingersoll Rand collaborates with Smile Foundation for Doorstep Healthcare Services

content.rendered:
Ingersoll Rand and Smile Foundation join hands to boost healthcare in Ahmedabad

Ingersoll Rand has partnered with Smile Foundation to enhance healthcare delivery in Ahmedabad through the Smile on Wheels project. This initiative brings vital medical services to communities in need, making healthcare more accessible and effective for local residents.

Ingersoll Rand collaborates with Smile Foundation for Doorstep Healthcare Services

Underserved urban slum dwellers of Ahmedabad are receiving quality healthcare services through Smile Foundation’s Smile on Wheels, a collaborative initiative with Ingersoll Rand. This partnership brings the hospital to the doorsteps of those who need it the most. The project has reached 46,422 beneficiaries till now, making a significant difference in the lives of the community members.

 

Ingersoll Rand joins hands with Smile Foundation to support the education of poor children

 

Ingersoll Rand has joined hands with Smile Foundation to support theMission Education Programme since the year 2015-16, Ingersoll is supporting basic/primary education of 200 underprivileged children each in Kolkata and Sahibabad. Further expanding the support in 2016-17, Ingersoll supported another Mission Education centre in Kolkata for providing secondary education to 200 underprivileged children.

Ingersoll-Rand plc is an Irish global diversified industrial manufacturing company formed in 1905 by the merger of Ingersoll-Sergeant Drill Company and Rand Drill Company, rival companies that had each been founded in 1871. The company is incorporated in Dublin, Ireland, and has its US operations headquartered in Davidson, North Carolina. Ingersoll-Rand has been a constituent of the S&P 500 Index since 2010; replacing Pactiv Corporation on 16 November 2010 (it had previously been in the S&P 500 Index until it was replaced by Quanta Services in June 2009).
